[[File:JeronFusionCutter.png|thumb|As seen from the user's point of view]]

A '''[[Jeron/Legends|Jeron]] [[Fusioncutter/Legends|fusioncutter]]''' was a portable mining tool used to cut rock. It was powered with [[Power cell/Legends|power cells]] and fired green bolts from each of its four chambers; it had the option to fire all four simultaneously, although this drained eight times the energy, instead of four times.<ref name="Dark Forces Manual: Coded Transmissions">''[[Dark Forces Manual: Coded Transmissions]]''</ref>

It could also be used as a weapon, as [[Kyle Katarn]] demonstrated on [[Gromas 16]]. Fire from all its four barrels provided wider range but less clout. Not designed as a weapon, its shots lost accuracy over distance, and it fired too slow for close combat.<ref name="DFPG" />

{{Tech-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
During development of the game the Fusion Cutter was one of the universally strongest weapons that outperform all others; its power was rationalised in the finished game in order to encourage more diverse strategy from the player.<ref name="DFPG">''[[Dark Forces Official Player's Guide]]''</ref>

